01:16:34.660 --> 01:16:36.773
and carbon-to-value real quickly.

01:16:38.090 --> 01:16:41.600
So submarines and spacecraft
if you've ever been in one,

01:16:41.600 --> 01:16:42.990
in their natural environment,

01:16:42.990 --> 01:16:44.723
guess what happens to the co2?

01:16:45.770 --> 01:16:47.490
They take it out.

01:16:47.490 --> 01:16:50.590
So taking co2 out has been done forever,

01:16:50.590 --> 01:16:54.380
you may remember Apollo 13
where one of the canisters

01:16:54.380 --> 01:16:58.750
was around and the other was
square and they had a problem,

01:16:58.750 --> 01:17:00.330
they were fitting one into the other.

01:17:00.330 --> 01:17:02.690
So knowing how to do it,
it's just doing it at scale

01:17:02.690 --> 01:17:04.700
and doing it affordably.

01:17:04.700 --> 01:17:08.123
But there's two sources, you
can take concentrated co2

01:17:09.680 --> 01:17:13.150
and that's out of the smokestack
or you can take it out

01:17:13.150 --> 01:17:15.550
of the air which is much harder to do.

01:17:15.550 --> 01:17:18.830
So recently the Carbon XPRIZE,
just to give you some hope,

01:17:18.830 --> 01:17:21.270
offered a $20,000,000 prize for people

01:17:21.270 --> 01:17:24.480
that could take carbon,
from either source,

01:17:24.480 --> 01:17:27.340
and converted into something
you could actually sell.

01:17:27.340 --> 01:17:29.820
So some examples here, C2CNT,

01:17:29.820 --> 01:17:32.570
not cleverest name I ever saw,

01:17:32.570 --> 01:17:35.650
it transforms co2 flue
gas into a carbon nanotube

01:17:35.650 --> 01:17:40.020
which you can then build into
airplanes wings, for example.

01:17:40.020 --> 01:17:42.748
So the carbon is now captured
in a structure that's,

01:17:42.748 --> 01:17:46.890
you know, it's a physical
structure that's of value.

01:17:46.890 --> 01:17:51.890
Another example here is CAX
which is based in Hayward,

01:17:52.760 --> 01:17:55.830
a local example, they convert the gas

01:17:55.830 --> 01:17:59.010
to ethylene glycol which is an ingredient

01:17:59.010 --> 01:18:02.033
in lithium-ion batteries
and a lot of other things.

01:18:03.064 --> 01:18:06.500
Kiverdi takes these
certain type of microbes

01:18:06.500 --> 01:18:09.343
add co2 and then convert
it into protein and oils.

01:18:10.280 --> 01:18:14.330
So the dream here and it has
to be some amount of reality,

01:18:14.330 --> 01:18:16.050
is that there'll be certain markets

01:18:16.050 --> 01:18:18.590
that can be figured out,
that can take carbon

01:18:19.525 --> 01:18:21.760
either dense at first
and maybe change later

01:18:21.760 --> 01:18:23.340
and convert it in the value.

